WEBVTT

1
00:00:05.093 --> 00:00:09.628
Narrator: In this
world. there is real evil

2
00:00:09.630 --> 00:00:13.632
in the darkest shadows and
in the most ordinary places.

3
00:00:14.636 --> 00:00:16.703
These are the true
stories of the innocent

4
00:00:16.705 --> 00:00:18.705
and the unimaginable.

5
00:00:20.976 --> 00:00:24.310
Cindy sarrow and her family
moved back to her hometown.

6
00:00:24.312 --> 00:00:26.012
hoping for a better life.

7
00:00:27.449 --> 00:00:30.049
But something sinister
lurks in the shadows.

8
00:00:30.051 --> 00:00:32.785
waiting to make its move.

9
00:00:32.787 --> 00:00:34.254
Desperate to
protect her children

10
00:00:34.256 --> 00:00:36.156
from something she cannot see...

11
00:00:37.525 --> 00:00:40.660
she becomes caught in
a supernatural nightmare

12
00:00:40.662 --> 00:00:42.395
she cannot escape.

13
00:00:44.332 --> 00:00:46.666
[ Whispering ]

14
00:00:46.668 --> 00:00:51.738
Between the world we
see and the things we fear.

15
00:00:51.740 --> 00:00:53.873
there are doors.

16
00:00:53.875 --> 00:00:56.543
When they are opened...

17
00:00:56.545 --> 00:01:00.080
Nightmares become reality.

18
00:01:07.421 --> 00:01:09.489
Even the most innocuous places

19
00:01:09.491 --> 00:01:12.959
bear the scars
of a twisted past.

20
00:01:12.961 --> 00:01:16.162
Evil can echo through time.

21
00:01:16.164 --> 00:01:20.232
lying dormant until
the unsuspecting

22
00:01:20.234 --> 00:01:25.472
unknowingly cross its
path. And the ill-prepared

23
00:01:35.717 --> 00:01:38.451
On the outskirts of St. Louis

24
00:01:38.453 --> 00:01:42.054
sits the township
of belleville. Illinois.

25
00:01:42.056 --> 00:01:45.792
Like many small cities and towns
that dot the midwest landscape.

26
00:01:45.794 --> 00:01:49.028
it has remained the
same for decades.

27
00:01:52.867 --> 00:01:55.435
The year is 1991.

28
00:01:58.473 --> 00:02:00.339
34-year-old Cindy sarrow

29
00:02:00.341 --> 00:02:03.543
has lived in the small
town for the past two years.

30
00:02:06.214 --> 00:02:12.152
Tonight. Cindy can't shake the
feeling that something is wrong.

31
00:02:32.774 --> 00:02:35.275
[ Growling ]

32
00:02:43.784 --> 00:02:46.853
[ Growling continues ]

33
00:03:00.001 --> 00:03:01.301
[ Dog barking ]

34
00:03:07.542 --> 00:03:10.243
[ Growling ]

35
00:03:28.563 --> 00:03:30.463
[ Stairs creak ]

36
00:03:31.433 --> 00:03:33.199
[ Screams ]

37
00:03:37.639 --> 00:03:40.773
Cindy: I just thought
it was a nightmare.

38
00:03:40.775 --> 00:03:44.210
but then I kept having it over
and over... the same dream.

39
00:03:50.651 --> 00:03:54.854
In my dreams. I was
fearing for my life.

40
00:03:54.856 --> 00:03:59.725
And I knew that whatever
this was was trying to kill me.

41
00:03:59.727 --> 00:04:01.227
I just felt it.

42
00:04:20.348 --> 00:04:22.147
Here you go. honey.

43
00:04:22.149 --> 00:04:23.816
What do you think
the surprise will be?

44
00:04:23.818 --> 00:04:26.152
Narrator: Cindy is
at stay-at-home mom.

45
00:04:26.154 --> 00:04:27.687
She has two children...

46
00:04:27.689 --> 00:04:31.357
7-year-old christie
and 9-year-old Brooke.

47
00:04:31.359 --> 00:04:33.359
Brooke: Me and my
family are really close.

48
00:04:33.361 --> 00:04:35.495
and it seemed that
nothing could tear us apart.

49
00:04:35.497 --> 00:04:38.898
When's daddy gonna get
here? He's taking forever.

50
00:04:38.900 --> 00:04:41.701
He'll be here in
just a few minutes.

51
00:04:41.703 --> 00:04:43.703
Honey. relax and
eat your breakfast.

52
00:04:43.705 --> 00:04:45.371
I can't.

53
00:04:45.373 --> 00:04:47.640
I'm too excited
about the surprise.

54
00:04:47.642 --> 00:04:49.575
What do you think it is?

55
00:04:49.577 --> 00:04:51.643
I have no idea.

56
00:04:51.645 --> 00:04:54.013
but I bet whatever
it is. it's wonderful.

57
00:04:55.783 --> 00:04:56.983
Dad's home.

58
00:04:56.985 --> 00:04:59.252
Narrator: Cindy's
longtime boyfriend. Jake.

59
00:04:59.254 --> 00:05:01.721
works the graveyard shift at
a chemical plant in St. Louis.

60
00:05:01.723 --> 00:05:03.790
How are my little
ladies today. hmm?

61
00:05:03.792 --> 00:05:05.725
[ Smooches ]

62
00:05:05.727 --> 00:05:07.226
Hey.

63
00:05:07.228 --> 00:05:09.228
Hi. honey.

64
00:05:10.197 --> 00:05:11.864
Everyone ready
for my big surprise?

65
00:05:11.866 --> 00:05:13.266
What is it?

66
00:05:13.268 --> 00:05:16.002
Well. you know how
we've been wanting

67
00:05:16.004 --> 00:05:18.137
to move back to caseyville.

68
00:05:18.139 --> 00:05:20.807
closer to your mother.
closer to work for me?

69
00:05:22.743 --> 00:05:24.143
What is it?

70
00:05:24.145 --> 00:05:26.479
Tell us. daddy! What's
the big surprise?

71
00:05:26.481 --> 00:05:27.947
Girls...

72
00:05:29.150 --> 00:05:30.917
go get dressed
and I'll show you.

73
00:05:35.022 --> 00:05:36.889
I think...

74
00:05:36.891 --> 00:05:38.958
I think I found that dream home.

75
00:05:43.832 --> 00:05:46.699
Narrator: Both Cindy and
Jake grew up in caseyville.

76
00:05:46.701 --> 00:05:50.203
a rural town at the base of
the Mississippi river bluffs.

77
00:05:55.977 --> 00:05:58.845
For months. they've talked about
moving back to their hometown

78
00:05:58.847 --> 00:06:01.948
and raising their family there.

79
00:06:03.117 --> 00:06:05.184
Uh-huh.

80
00:06:05.186 --> 00:06:07.954
Come on! Hop to!

81
00:06:17.265 --> 00:06:19.799
Be careful. you two!

82
00:06:19.801 --> 00:06:21.600
So. what do you think?

83
00:06:21.602 --> 00:06:23.803
It's nice.

84
00:06:23.805 --> 00:06:25.538
I really like it.

85
00:06:25.540 --> 00:06:28.073
But do we have the
money for a place like this?

86
00:06:28.075 --> 00:06:29.675
Barely. but yes.

87
00:06:29.677 --> 00:06:31.610
Cindy: It was a house
that we could afford.

88
00:06:31.612 --> 00:06:34.147
but we were really
financially strapped.

89
00:06:34.149 --> 00:06:36.815
There was things that
needed to be done to the house.

90
00:06:36.817 --> 00:06:40.085
We would have to come
up with the money for that.

91
00:06:40.087 --> 00:06:43.489
Sounds like it's gonna take a
lot of money and a lot of work.

92
00:06:43.491 --> 00:06:44.757
I know. honey. I know.

93
00:06:44.759 --> 00:06:47.627
but there aren't a lot of
houses up for sale right now.

94
00:06:47.629 --> 00:06:51.497
and it might be years before
we get another chance like this.

95
00:06:51.499 --> 00:06:52.831
Now. you've always talked about

96
00:06:52.833 --> 00:06:55.167
how much you've wanted
to raise our family here.

97
00:06:55.169 --> 00:06:58.771
It really is a great house.

98
00:06:58.773 --> 00:07:00.773
It is a great house.

99
00:07:00.775 --> 00:07:03.109
Yeah? All right!

100
00:07:03.111 --> 00:07:04.177
[ Laughs ]

101
00:07:04.179 --> 00:07:06.179
We were real excited.

102
00:07:06.181 --> 00:07:07.513
We weren't renting.

103
00:07:07.515 --> 00:07:10.116
We'd have our own
home and just be happy.

104
00:07:10.118 --> 00:07:11.917
Isn't that great?

105
00:07:11.919 --> 00:07:13.118
All right?

106
00:07:13.120 --> 00:07:16.656
We can fit our TV
right through there.

107
00:07:28.068 --> 00:07:30.136
Mom! What are you doing here?

108
00:07:30.138 --> 00:07:33.072
Narrator: Cindy is grateful to
be near her ailing mother. Anita.

109
00:07:33.074 --> 00:07:36.275
who suffers from a
degenerative disease.

110
00:07:36.277 --> 00:07:39.879
Cindy: She was sick.
and she was getting sicker.

111
00:07:39.881 --> 00:07:41.347
and I just wanted
to be close to her

112
00:07:41.349 --> 00:07:44.417
to be able to help
her and be with her.

113
00:07:44.419 --> 00:07:47.219
Grandma's here! Grandma!

114
00:07:47.221 --> 00:07:48.688
Oh. so good to see you!

115
00:07:48.690 --> 00:07:50.222
Want to see my new room?

116
00:07:50.224 --> 00:07:52.357
Our new room. Sure.

117
00:07:52.359 --> 00:07:53.893
Girls. take grandma
inside. Okay.

118
00:08:00.168 --> 00:08:02.969
I'll get the rest of the boxes.

119
00:08:02.971 --> 00:08:04.837
You should start unpacking.

120
00:08:04.839 --> 00:08:06.238
That's a great idea.

121
00:08:06.240 --> 00:08:08.007
Thanks. honey.

122
00:08:14.849 --> 00:08:17.116
[ Cabinet door squeaks ]

123
00:09:21.382 --> 00:09:22.615
Jake!

124
00:09:26.921 --> 00:09:29.121
The cabinet doors
are falling off!

125
00:09:29.123 --> 00:09:30.856
I think it's just the
hinges on these doors

126
00:09:30.858 --> 00:09:32.458
are just a little too old.

127
00:09:32.460 --> 00:09:35.461
Cindy: I had doubts
about the house.

128
00:09:35.463 --> 00:09:37.529
I thought. "what
did I buy here?"

129
00:09:37.531 --> 00:09:38.931
I guess you're right.

130
00:09:38.933 --> 00:09:41.600
I should expect things
like this to happen.

131
00:09:41.602 --> 00:09:43.669
It is a pretty old house.

132
00:09:43.671 --> 00:09:44.803
Exactly.

133
00:09:44.805 --> 00:09:47.273
Now. where did I put my tools?

134
00:09:59.620 --> 00:10:01.553
Narrator: That night.

135
00:10:01.555 --> 00:10:04.657
Cindy helps her daughters
set up their new room.

136
00:10:18.106 --> 00:10:20.706
[ Electricity crackling ]

137
00:10:36.523 --> 00:10:40.793
Oh. looks like that
bulb's about to go.

138
00:10:40.795 --> 00:10:43.763
Hold on. girls. while I go
look for another light bulb.

139
00:10:49.069 --> 00:10:52.571
The bedroom had a
very eerie feeling to it.

140
00:10:55.476 --> 00:10:57.142
I just had a horrible feeling

141
00:10:57.144 --> 00:10:59.678
that something was
wrong with the house.

142
00:10:59.680 --> 00:11:01.313
[ Crackling continues ]

143
00:11:09.757 --> 00:11:13.358
Whoa. Where are
you running off to?

144
00:11:13.360 --> 00:11:14.894
[ Breathing heavily ]

145
00:11:14.896 --> 00:11:16.162
What's the matter?

146
00:11:16.164 --> 00:11:19.431
'Cause I wasn't sure myself
about what was going on...

147
00:11:19.433 --> 00:11:22.434
We had just moved there...
That I didn't want to worry her.

148
00:11:22.436 --> 00:11:24.170
It's okay. honey.
You can tell me.

149
00:11:24.172 --> 00:11:26.105
I don't like my room. mom.

150
00:11:26.107 --> 00:11:27.840
What do you mean?
It's a great room.

151
00:11:27.842 --> 00:11:29.308
It's perfect for you guys.

152
00:11:29.310 --> 00:11:31.409
I don't know.

153
00:11:31.411 --> 00:11:33.846
There's something
creepy about it.

154
00:11:33.848 --> 00:11:34.980
I can't sleep in there.

155
00:11:34.982 --> 00:11:36.982
I don't want to
sleep in there either.

156
00:11:36.984 --> 00:11:38.450
Oh. you guys don't
have to be scared.

157
00:11:38.452 --> 00:11:40.319
Your father and I will
be right here with you.

158
00:11:40.321 --> 00:11:42.321
Mom. no!

159
00:11:41.122 --> 00:11:42.455
Brooke!

160
00:11:42.457 --> 00:11:45.191
You are too old to
be acting like this.

161
00:11:45.193 --> 00:11:46.458
I expect more from you.

162
00:11:46.460 --> 00:11:48.527
But. daddy... no "buts." okay?

163
00:11:48.529 --> 00:11:51.997
Now. that's where you girls
are sleeping. and that's final.

164
00:11:53.400 --> 00:11:54.933
Can you do it for me?

165
00:11:54.935 --> 00:11:58.203
[ Sighs ] Okay. I'll do it.

166
00:11:58.205 --> 00:11:59.872
Jake: That's my girl.

167
00:12:02.076 --> 00:12:04.477
Thank you. honey.

168
00:12:09.083 --> 00:12:11.117
Narrator: Later that night...

169
00:12:19.093 --> 00:12:21.760
as if seeing her
house for the first time.

170
00:12:21.762 --> 00:12:24.964
Cindy has a sudden revelation.

171
00:12:24.966 --> 00:12:27.232
Cindy: I couldn't believe it.

172
00:12:27.234 --> 00:12:31.003
It was the same stairs
that are in my nightmares.

173
00:12:33.507 --> 00:12:36.809
[ Breathing heavily ]

174
00:12:46.854 --> 00:12:51.723
I was really afraid.
but what could I do?

175
00:12:51.725 --> 00:12:53.993
Narrator: Cindy knows that
Jake would never consider moving

176
00:12:53.995 --> 00:12:56.428
because of an eerie feeling.

177
00:13:02.002 --> 00:13:04.536
[ Gasps ]

178
00:13:04.538 --> 00:13:06.538
You okay?

179
00:13:05.539 --> 00:13:07.139
Look like you've seen a ghost.

180
00:13:07.141 --> 00:13:09.942
Yeah. I'm okay.

181
00:13:09.944 --> 00:13:11.276
Just a little tired. that's all.

182
00:13:11.278 --> 00:13:12.477
All right.

183
00:13:12.479 --> 00:13:14.213
You ready for work?

184
00:13:14.215 --> 00:13:17.683
Yeah. In fact.
I'm a little late.

185
00:13:17.685 --> 00:13:19.685
Do you think maybe
you could play hooky?

186
00:13:19.687 --> 00:13:21.620
You know. maybe call
in sick or something?

187
00:13:21.622 --> 00:13:23.555
What. you getting
freaked out. too?

188
00:13:23.557 --> 00:13:25.157
It's no wonder
Brooke and christie

189
00:13:25.159 --> 00:13:27.092
don't want to
sleep in their room.

190
00:13:27.094 --> 00:13:29.161
Like mother. like daughters.

191
00:13:29.163 --> 00:13:31.296
You'll be okay. all right?

192
00:13:31.298 --> 00:13:32.698
[ Smooches ]

193
00:13:32.700 --> 00:13:35.434
If you need me. give
me a call at work.

194
00:13:35.436 --> 00:13:38.237
If you don't. I'll see
you in the morning.

195
00:13:38.239 --> 00:13:39.705
Okay.

196
00:14:11.005 --> 00:14:15.374
Brooke: It seemed like
every hour. I was waking up.

197
00:14:17.211 --> 00:14:20.813
I had this feeling that
someone was there.

198
00:14:20.815 --> 00:14:24.149
watching me. but I
couldn't see anyone.

199
00:15:11.298 --> 00:15:13.766
[ Electricity crackles ]

200
00:15:17.838 --> 00:15:19.704
Narrator: A few weeks later.

201
00:15:19.706 --> 00:15:23.309
Cindy finally begins to
feel settled in her new home.

202
00:15:38.792 --> 00:15:40.125
Come on. girls.

203
00:15:40.127 --> 00:15:41.794
You have your own beds.

204
00:15:41.796 --> 00:15:44.063
Why don't you sleep in our room?

205
00:15:44.065 --> 00:15:46.265
Because your bed's too small.

206
00:15:46.267 --> 00:15:47.532
Now. come on. Let's go.

207
00:15:47.534 --> 00:15:51.003
But. mom. I can't. Please.

208
00:15:51.005 --> 00:15:52.270
I couldn't go back in there.

209
00:15:52.272 --> 00:15:55.274
I couldn't sleep in
there. I was afraid. really.

210
00:15:55.276 --> 00:15:56.675
I think that's what
it comes down to...

211
00:15:56.677 --> 00:15:58.343
I was just really afraid.

212
00:15:58.345 --> 00:16:01.080
All right. I'll
sleep on the sofa.

213
00:16:01.082 --> 00:16:04.750
But sooner or later.
this has got to end.

214
00:16:04.752 --> 00:16:06.418
Good night. Good night. mom.

215
00:16:06.420 --> 00:16:08.721
Good night. baby.

216
00:16:12.359 --> 00:16:15.260
Sleep tight.

217
00:16:45.258 --> 00:16:47.826
[ Creaking ]

218
00:17:07.882 --> 00:17:10.082
[ Creaking continues ]

219
00:17:19.960 --> 00:17:21.826
Narrator: Cindy
fears that someone

220
00:17:21.828 --> 00:17:24.296
may have broken into the house.

221
00:17:27.101 --> 00:17:29.434
Cindy: I was afraid for
my children and myself

222
00:17:29.436 --> 00:17:32.438
because we were
home by ourselves.

223
00:18:24.558 --> 00:18:26.391
Mom? [ Gasps ]

224
00:18:27.228 --> 00:18:29.828
What are you doing?

225
00:18:29.830 --> 00:18:31.095
Honey. what are you doing up?

226
00:18:31.097 --> 00:18:32.697
I was thirsty.

227
00:18:32.699 --> 00:18:34.299
What are you doing?

228
00:18:34.301 --> 00:18:37.101
I thought I heard a noise.

229
00:18:37.103 --> 00:18:39.103
You really scared me.

230
00:18:39.105 --> 00:18:41.840
I know. You jumped
like 10 feet in the air.

231
00:18:41.842 --> 00:18:45.443
All right. Now you
need to get to bed.

232
00:18:45.445 --> 00:18:47.445
Night. mom.

233
00:18:56.523 --> 00:18:58.123
Narrator: The following night.

234
00:18:58.125 --> 00:19:02.661
Cindy calls her mother.
Anita. to see how she's feeling.

235
00:19:02.663 --> 00:19:05.464
She lives in a one-bedroom
apartment across town.

236
00:19:05.466 --> 00:19:07.065
Anita: I don't know
what happened.

237
00:19:07.067 --> 00:19:10.202
and all of a sudden.
my head started to spin.

238
00:19:10.204 --> 00:19:12.404
Should I stop by your place?

239
00:19:12.406 --> 00:19:15.274
I appreciate the offer.
but don't bother. honey.

240
00:19:15.276 --> 00:19:17.942
I think what I need is
just to rest for a while.

241
00:19:17.944 --> 00:19:20.479
Okay. Sounds good.

242
00:19:20.481 --> 00:19:22.681
Well. I guess I'll
see you tomorrow.

243
00:19:22.683 --> 00:19:24.283
Okay. Sure.

244
00:19:25.952 --> 00:19:28.820
Is everything all right?

245
00:19:30.958 --> 00:19:35.026
Mom. I think that
the house is...

246
00:19:35.028 --> 00:19:37.095
[ Static hissing ]

247
00:19:37.764 --> 00:19:39.431
Cindy?

248
00:19:39.433 --> 00:19:42.034
Look. mom. everything's
fine. I got to go.

249
00:20:22.542 --> 00:20:25.677
Narrator: With all the strange
things occurring in the house...

250
00:20:31.885 --> 00:20:34.953
Cindy begins to
have trouble sleeping.

251
00:20:49.836 --> 00:20:52.170
[ Screams ]

252
00:20:52.172 --> 00:20:53.305
[ Gasps ]

253
00:20:53.307 --> 00:20:55.641
[ Breathing heavily ]

254
00:21:01.048 --> 00:21:02.581
Cindy: I couldn't
go black to sleep

255
00:21:02.583 --> 00:21:06.117
because I just felt there
was somebody staring at me.

256
00:21:06.119 --> 00:21:09.921
I knew somebody was
there. but I couldn't see them.

257
00:21:09.923 --> 00:21:13.325
I could just feel
their presence.

258
00:21:19.266 --> 00:21:21.099
Narrator: The next morning.

259
00:21:32.746 --> 00:21:35.447
Cindy: I was pushed
so hard that I went down.

260
00:21:48.228 --> 00:21:52.230
Narrator: Cindy is hesitant to
tell Jake what just happened.

261
00:21:52.232 --> 00:21:54.800
She can barely
believe it herself.

262
00:22:05.045 --> 00:22:06.845
Jake?

263
00:22:06.847 --> 00:22:08.179
Wake up.

264
00:22:08.181 --> 00:22:10.515
Jake.

265
00:22:10.517 --> 00:22:12.984
There's something
wrong with this place.

266
00:22:12.986 --> 00:22:16.120
Not the electricity again.

267
00:22:16.122 --> 00:22:19.391
No. it's not that.

268
00:22:19.393 --> 00:22:23.327
Jake. I don't think
I can live here.

269
00:22:23.329 --> 00:22:25.130
Oh. no.

270
00:22:25.132 --> 00:22:28.867
Look. honey. I know there's
been a lot of repairs lately.

271
00:22:28.869 --> 00:22:30.068
but that'll end.

272
00:22:30.070 --> 00:22:32.270
I just don't feel safe.

273
00:22:32.272 --> 00:22:35.273
And I don't think the
girls feel safe either.

274
00:22:35.275 --> 00:22:37.409
Well... i can get an
alarm system if you want.

275
00:22:37.411 --> 00:22:42.413
I don't want an alarm system.
I want a different house.

276
00:22:42.415 --> 00:22:44.616
Oh. Cindy. Cindy. come on.

277
00:22:44.618 --> 00:22:48.086
Don't be ridiculous.
We just moved in.

278
00:22:48.088 --> 00:22:50.021
Cindy: How can I tell
somebody what's going on here

279
00:22:50.023 --> 00:22:53.425
when it's so bizarre. everything
that was happening. you know?

280
00:22:53.427 --> 00:22:54.692
Who's gonna believe it?

281
00:22:54.694 --> 00:22:57.562
You know we can't afford it.

282
00:23:00.567 --> 00:23:04.970
I know you're not too
thrilled with the house.

283
00:23:04.972 --> 00:23:08.172
but just give it some time.

284
00:23:08.174 --> 00:23:09.841
Please?

285
00:23:09.843 --> 00:23:13.377
I don't think I can.

286
00:23:13.379 --> 00:23:15.379
Fine.

287
00:23:14.381 --> 00:23:16.515
Please fill me in
on how you plan

288
00:23:16.517 --> 00:23:18.316
to come up with all this money!

289
00:23:18.318 --> 00:23:21.186
I don't know! But
I'll figure it out!

290
00:23:31.532 --> 00:23:33.665
Brooke: That upset me. because
when we lived in belleville.

291
00:23:33.667 --> 00:23:35.132
they always got along.

292
00:23:35.134 --> 00:23:39.271
and now it seemed that my
mother and father were fighting a lot.

293
00:23:39.273 --> 00:23:41.273
Come on. girls.

294
00:23:55.956 --> 00:23:58.890
Narrator: Weeks pass...

295
00:23:58.892 --> 00:24:01.693
And the strange
activity continues.

296
00:24:05.499 --> 00:24:07.432
Although Cindy is
not a religious person.

297
00:24:07.434 --> 00:24:10.168
she begins to pray
on a regular basis.

298
00:24:25.252 --> 00:24:29.588
She wonders if she can
find comfort in her faith.

299
00:24:32.926 --> 00:24:35.861
Cindy: I put up a
picture of Jesus.

300
00:24:35.863 --> 00:24:38.563
I felt like that was
protection for us.

301
00:24:42.202 --> 00:24:43.935
Jake: Cindy.

302
00:24:45.472 --> 00:24:46.905
Cindy. come here.

303
00:24:51.278 --> 00:24:53.879
What is it. Jake?

304
00:24:58.151 --> 00:25:00.185
Jake?

305
00:25:26.246 --> 00:25:27.646
[ Gasping ]

306
00:25:30.717 --> 00:25:34.452
[ Crying ]

307
00:25:34.454 --> 00:25:37.088
I was scared half to death.

308
00:25:54.207 --> 00:25:55.607
Cindy. are you okay?

309
00:25:55.609 --> 00:25:57.542
It's all right. It's all right.

310
00:25:57.544 --> 00:25:59.810
Did you hurt yourself?
What's going on?

311
00:25:59.812 --> 00:26:02.079
Something attacked me.
and then I couldn't breathe!

312
00:26:02.081 --> 00:26:04.415
Okay. Slow down. slow
down. Take a deep breath.

313
00:26:04.417 --> 00:26:05.450
Tell me.

314
00:26:07.888 --> 00:26:10.755
There's a ghost in this house.

315
00:26:10.757 --> 00:26:12.690
Come on. honey.
Tell me the truth.

316
00:26:12.692 --> 00:26:15.226
Tell me what happened.
No. I'm being serious. Jake.

317
00:26:15.228 --> 00:26:17.161
There's something here.
and it's trying to hurt me.

318
00:26:17.163 --> 00:26:21.366
Sweetie. it's just us. It's
just in your imagination.

319
00:26:21.368 --> 00:26:23.501
No! You're not listening to me!

320
00:26:23.503 --> 00:26:25.836
There's something in this
house. and it's trying to kill me.

321
00:26:25.838 --> 00:26:27.171
and you don't even care!

322
00:26:27.173 --> 00:26:30.508
Of course I care. but try to
be reasonable here. Cindy.

323
00:26:30.510 --> 00:26:33.578
There... there's
nothing in this house.

324
00:26:33.580 --> 00:26:35.913
I can't live here.

325
00:26:35.915 --> 00:26:38.316
Jake. it tried to suffocate me!

326
00:26:38.318 --> 00:26:40.718
Cindy. [ Sighs ]

327
00:26:40.720 --> 00:26:43.655
This house is not haunted. okay?

328
00:26:43.657 --> 00:26:47.058
Ghosts do not exist.

329
00:26:47.060 --> 00:26:50.061
I wish I never let you
convince me to buy this house.

330
00:26:50.063 --> 00:26:51.663
Are you kidding me?

331
00:26:51.665 --> 00:26:54.599
You wanted this
house as much as I did!

332
00:26:54.601 --> 00:26:57.135
What's gotten into you lately?

333
00:26:57.137 --> 00:26:58.202
Jake. I'm scared!

334
00:26:58.204 --> 00:27:00.872
We sunk our life
savings into this house!

335
00:27:00.874 --> 00:27:03.340
We are not moving.
and that's final.

336
00:27:04.144 --> 00:27:06.544
Cindy: I couldn't
take it anymore.

337
00:27:06.546 --> 00:27:08.647
I needed help.

338
00:27:23.563 --> 00:27:25.763
I started calling
different churches.

339
00:27:25.765 --> 00:27:29.367
and nobody wanted to help me.

340
00:27:29.369 --> 00:27:33.237
Finally. I spoke with a priest.
and he was going to help me.

341
00:27:33.239 --> 00:27:35.306
Narrator: In the nearby
town of belleville...

342
00:27:35.308 --> 00:27:37.976
Cindy: My life's
falling apart. father.

343
00:27:37.978 --> 00:27:39.243
I just don't know what to do.

344
00:27:39.245 --> 00:27:40.845
Cindy meets with father Thomas.

345
00:27:40.847 --> 00:27:43.647
From what you've told me.

346
00:27:43.649 --> 00:27:46.451
it appears as though
it may be demonic.

347
00:27:48.221 --> 00:27:50.788
The first step is
to bless the house.

348
00:27:50.790 --> 00:27:53.324
That may drive the demon out.

349
00:27:53.326 --> 00:27:55.794
But I'll need some
time to prepare.

350
00:27:55.796 --> 00:27:57.328
I'll have to fast and pray

351
00:27:57.330 --> 00:27:59.597
before I can actually
conduct the blessing.

352
00:27:59.599 --> 00:28:02.400
I understand. father. I'm
so grateful for your help.

353
00:28:04.738 --> 00:28:06.805
Here.

354
00:28:06.807 --> 00:28:11.943
When you're afraid.
read psalm 91.

355
00:28:11.945 --> 00:28:14.412
It will protect you from evil.

356
00:28:14.414 --> 00:28:16.114
Thank you again. father.

357
00:28:28.628 --> 00:28:30.494
Narrator: That night.

358
00:28:30.496 --> 00:28:33.731
Cindy anxiously waits
for Jake to come home.

359
00:28:33.733 --> 00:28:36.567
She keeps herself calm
by reading the Bible.

360
00:28:36.569 --> 00:28:38.703
[ Gravel crunching ]

361
00:28:44.243 --> 00:28:47.078
[ Engine idling ]

362
00:28:53.986 --> 00:28:56.020
[ Insects chirping ]

363
00:29:11.538 --> 00:29:13.138
Jake?

364
00:29:33.560 --> 00:29:34.993
[ Screams ]

365
00:29:42.035 --> 00:29:43.568
Please hurry!

366
00:29:52.712 --> 00:29:54.578
[ Screaming ]

367
00:29:54.580 --> 00:29:55.747
[ Screams ]

368
00:30:07.894 --> 00:30:10.128
[ Siren wailing ]

369
00:30:10.130 --> 00:30:13.064
Police department!
Put the ax down!

370
00:30:13.066 --> 00:30:15.400
Cindy: I was relieved to see
the police when they came.

371
00:30:15.402 --> 00:30:16.668
It was like. "thank god."

372
00:30:16.670 --> 00:30:18.670
Put your hands behind your head.

373
00:30:18.672 --> 00:30:21.672
He had chopped the
door down with the ax.

374
00:30:21.674 --> 00:30:23.207
Thank god they made it in time

375
00:30:23.209 --> 00:30:26.611
before he did whatever
he was out to do.

376
00:30:26.613 --> 00:30:29.314
[ Indistinct radio chatter ]

377
00:30:38.090 --> 00:30:41.492
Man: Are you okay?

378
00:30:41.494 --> 00:30:45.163
Can you tell me
what happened here?

379
00:30:45.165 --> 00:30:47.298
Jake...

380
00:30:47.300 --> 00:30:51.436
I don't know. He just...
He didn't look right.

381
00:30:51.438 --> 00:30:56.574
Narrator: Cindy believes
that Jake was possessed.

382
00:30:56.576 --> 00:30:58.576
Do you want to take
charges out on him?

383
00:30:58.578 --> 00:31:02.714
She now knows it was Jake
who tried to suffocate her.

384
00:31:04.050 --> 00:31:05.984
Ma'am?

385
00:31:05.986 --> 00:31:08.720
I'll think about it.

386
00:31:08.722 --> 00:31:10.655
Cindy does not press charges.

387
00:31:10.657 --> 00:31:13.892
believing that Jake's
will was not his own.

388
00:31:15.862 --> 00:31:19.797
But she does not allow
him back into the house.

389
00:31:19.799 --> 00:31:22.734
He moves in with his mother.

390
00:31:32.012 --> 00:31:35.680
An hour later. the girls
return from their movie.

391
00:31:40.286 --> 00:31:43.521
What happened to the door. mom?

392
00:31:45.624 --> 00:31:47.892
What's wrong. mom?

393
00:31:49.362 --> 00:31:52.363
Daddy's gonna have
to go away for a while.

394
00:31:52.365 --> 00:31:53.631
Why?

395
00:31:53.633 --> 00:31:57.035
It's really complicated.
but I'm trying to fix things.

396
00:31:57.037 --> 00:31:59.904
and maybe in a few weeks.
things will be normal again.

397
00:31:59.906 --> 00:32:01.505
Dad's not gonna be here at all?

398
00:32:01.507 --> 00:32:04.575
Brooke: When I found out my
dad wasn't gonna be around.

399
00:32:04.577 --> 00:32:07.245
I was really upset because
we were really close.

400
00:32:07.247 --> 00:32:09.514
and it just seemed like since
we moved into the house.

401
00:32:09.516 --> 00:32:12.383
our whole family
was falling apart.

402
00:32:12.385 --> 00:32:15.453
Don't you worry.
Everything is gonna be fine.

403
00:32:15.455 --> 00:32:17.722
I promise.

404
00:32:17.724 --> 00:32:19.057
Now go wash up.

405
00:32:19.059 --> 00:32:22.260
I'll be up in a few
minutes to tuck you in.

406
00:32:22.262 --> 00:32:23.728
Okay.

407
00:32:33.473 --> 00:32:35.673
[ Sobbing ]

408
00:32:57.831 --> 00:32:59.696
[ Screams ]

409
00:33:00.766 --> 00:33:04.268
Narrator: Cindy and the girls flee
to Anita's one-bedroom apartment.

410
00:33:06.039 --> 00:33:08.840
[ Crying ] It possessed Jake.
and he tried to attack me.

411
00:33:12.645 --> 00:33:14.244
I can't go back there!

412
00:33:14.246 --> 00:33:15.780
What if it tries
to hurt the girls?

413
00:33:15.782 --> 00:33:19.517
I was so relieved
that they were safe...

414
00:33:19.519 --> 00:33:22.086
And that we weren't
going back to the house.

415
00:33:25.458 --> 00:33:28.125
"The lord is my
refuge and my fortress.

416
00:33:28.127 --> 00:33:30.862
my god. in whom I trust.

417
00:33:30.864 --> 00:33:33.731
I will not fear the terror
that attacks by night.

418
00:33:33.733 --> 00:33:36.667
or the arrow that flies by day.

419
00:33:36.669 --> 00:33:39.336
No affliction will
enter my house.

420
00:33:39.338 --> 00:33:43.141
He will give his angels reign
over me to keep me safe."

421
00:33:43.143 --> 00:33:46.077
When I started
reciting psalms 91.

422
00:33:46.079 --> 00:33:48.479
I felt like I was
being protected.

423
00:33:48.481 --> 00:33:52.350
like god was with me and
he was gonna help me.

424
00:34:14.974 --> 00:34:16.307
The next thing I know.

425
00:34:16.309 --> 00:34:20.711
there's no house there where
my house should've been.

426
00:34:20.713 --> 00:34:21.913
I didn't understand it.

427
00:34:21.915 --> 00:34:24.115
I just think I was
in a different time.

428
00:34:24.117 --> 00:34:26.050
[ Distorted voices.
man chanting ]

429
00:34:37.796 --> 00:34:39.930
It was an answer to my prayer.

430
00:34:39.932 --> 00:34:43.935
telling me that something had
went on years and years ago.

431
00:35:03.222 --> 00:35:04.755
Narrator: The next day.

432
00:35:04.757 --> 00:35:07.958
Cindy goes to father Thomas
to tell him about her dream.

433
00:35:07.960 --> 00:35:09.893
These men were
performing a ceremony

434
00:35:09.895 --> 00:35:12.330
that had something
to do with the dead.

435
00:35:13.900 --> 00:35:17.268
They were digging up a body
where my house now stands.

436
00:35:20.973 --> 00:35:22.373
It sounds as though
you witnessed

437
00:35:22.375 --> 00:35:24.442
a ritual of necromancy.

438
00:35:24.444 --> 00:35:27.512
That's a form of
summoning a spirit. a demon.

439
00:35:27.514 --> 00:35:31.782
or a human soul
to enter a corpse.

440
00:35:31.784 --> 00:35:33.717
But why?

441
00:35:33.719 --> 00:35:35.386
Well. there are several reasons.

442
00:35:35.388 --> 00:35:38.789
but mainly. the goal is
to conjure up a demon.

443
00:35:38.791 --> 00:35:41.992
which explains the demonic
presence in your home.

444
00:35:42.862 --> 00:35:47.064
I'll be able to perform the
house blessing tomorrow.

445
00:35:47.066 --> 00:35:48.799
Thank you.

446
00:35:48.801 --> 00:35:51.068
But...

447
00:35:51.070 --> 00:35:54.138
I'm going to ask you to do
something you may not like.

448
00:35:54.140 --> 00:35:57.074
Anything. father. I
just want this to end.

449
00:35:57.076 --> 00:35:59.610
I need you and the
girls to be present

450
00:35:59.612 --> 00:36:01.913
while I perform the blessing.

451
00:36:04.284 --> 00:36:07.284
You must confront the demon

452
00:36:07.286 --> 00:36:11.088
in order to send
him to the other side.

453
00:36:11.958 --> 00:36:16.227
Well... i guess I
have no other choice.

454
00:36:16.229 --> 00:36:18.429
I really didn't want
any of us in the house.

455
00:36:18.431 --> 00:36:22.033
I would've much rather handed
him the key and let him do it.

456
00:36:22.035 --> 00:36:24.135
but it couldn't
be done that way.

457
00:36:30.109 --> 00:36:31.642
Narrator: Father Thomas knows

458
00:36:31.644 --> 00:36:34.044
that a demon is
highly unpredictable.

459
00:36:34.046 --> 00:36:37.782
It has already manifested
itself in different ways.

460
00:36:47.794 --> 00:36:49.927
Hi. father Thomas.

461
00:36:49.929 --> 00:36:50.995
Hello.

462
00:37:09.282 --> 00:37:12.116
Peace be in this house
and with all who live here.

463
00:37:13.152 --> 00:37:15.085
Lord god of heaven and earth.

464
00:37:15.087 --> 00:37:17.488
bless this house
and all who inhabit it.

465
00:37:17.490 --> 00:37:20.624
Cindy: I was still
scared. but I kept praying.

466
00:37:20.626 --> 00:37:23.160
I didn't want anybody hurt.

467
00:37:23.162 --> 00:37:25.896
and I just wanted
this to be over with.

468
00:37:25.898 --> 00:37:30.634
In the name of the father
and the son and the holy spirit.

469
00:37:30.636 --> 00:37:32.969
Lord god of heaven and earth.

470
00:37:32.971 --> 00:37:35.640
bless this house
and all who inhabit it.

471
00:37:35.642 --> 00:37:38.041
Fill them with
the light of Christ

472
00:37:38.043 --> 00:37:41.712
that their concerns for
others may reflect your love.

473
00:37:41.714 --> 00:37:44.115
We ask through Christ our lord

474
00:37:44.117 --> 00:37:48.853
in the name of the father
and the son and the holy spirit.

475
00:37:48.855 --> 00:37:50.788
Fill them with
the light of Christ

476
00:37:50.790 --> 00:37:54.191
that their concerns for
others may reflect your love.

477
00:37:54.193 --> 00:37:56.993
We ask through Christ our lord

478
00:37:56.995 --> 00:38:00.564
in the name of the father
and the son and the holy spirit.

479
00:38:05.338 --> 00:38:07.137
I can't thank you
enough. father.

480
00:38:07.139 --> 00:38:08.539
Of course. my dear.

481
00:38:08.541 --> 00:38:11.675
I'll always be here for
you in your time of need.

482
00:38:11.677 --> 00:38:13.511
Thank you.

483
00:38:16.081 --> 00:38:18.015
Goodbye.

484
00:38:18.017 --> 00:38:19.383
Bye.

485
00:38:22.955 --> 00:38:27.224
I felt relieved that we
finally had our house

486
00:38:27.226 --> 00:38:29.393
and there was no evil.

487
00:38:36.102 --> 00:38:37.768
Narrator: That night.

488
00:38:37.770 --> 00:38:40.571
Cindy and the girls
move back into the house.

489
00:38:57.457 --> 00:39:00.658
I felt my hair rise on my neck.

490
00:39:13.206 --> 00:39:15.072
Something grabbed me.

491
00:39:16.542 --> 00:39:18.042
Mom!

492
00:39:20.546 --> 00:39:22.613
[ Screams ]

493
00:39:22.615 --> 00:39:23.747
[ Electricity crackles ]

494
00:39:23.749 --> 00:39:25.749
What?!

495
00:39:24.684 --> 00:39:25.883
Mom! Brooke!

496
00:39:25.885 --> 00:39:27.818
[ Gasps ]

497
00:39:27.820 --> 00:39:30.687
No! You can't have my daughters!

498
00:39:30.689 --> 00:39:34.291
In the name of the
lord. let my daughter go!

499
00:39:34.293 --> 00:39:35.759
[ Screams ]

500
00:39:35.761 --> 00:39:38.695
[ Crying ] Oh. my
god! Oh. my god!

501
00:39:38.697 --> 00:39:40.431
Oh. my god! My baby!

502
00:39:40.433 --> 00:39:42.766
Oh. thank you. god.

503
00:39:42.768 --> 00:39:44.167
I was terrified.

504
00:39:44.169 --> 00:39:47.838
I've never. ever seen
anything so powerful in my life.

505
00:39:47.840 --> 00:39:50.774
Girls. come on. come on!
Come on. honey. Come on!

506
00:39:50.776 --> 00:39:54.645
Come on. run! Hurry!
Hurry. honey! Go!

507
00:39:54.647 --> 00:39:57.781
Run. honey! Come on. Come on.

508
00:39:57.783 --> 00:40:01.518
Come on. girls. Let's
just go. Go. go. go. go!

509
00:40:01.520 --> 00:40:02.920
Just go. girls!

510
00:40:05.324 --> 00:40:07.091
[ Crying ]

511
00:40:10.062 --> 00:40:13.931
I don't know. I don't know.
I don't know. I don't know!

512
00:40:13.933 --> 00:40:15.299
I don't know!

513
00:40:19.405 --> 00:40:21.238
[ Engine starts ]

514
00:40:37.089 --> 00:40:39.490
Narrator: Cindy and the
girls stay with her mother

515
00:40:39.492 --> 00:40:41.459
while she tries
to sell the house.

516
00:40:46.332 --> 00:40:49.767
Cindy and Jake are unable
to bridge the rift between them

517
00:40:49.769 --> 00:40:52.503
and decide to go
their separate ways.

518
00:40:54.106 --> 00:40:55.906
Cindy begins
working at a local hotel

519
00:40:55.908 --> 00:41:01.512
and eventually saves enough
money to purchase a new home.

520
00:41:01.514 --> 00:41:04.448
Jake maintains a relationship
with Brooke and christie.

521
00:41:04.450 --> 00:41:06.917
seeing them on weekends.

522
00:41:07.854 --> 00:41:10.921
Over time. Cindy and
her daughters' lives

523
00:41:10.923 --> 00:41:13.591
become peaceful once more.

524
00:41:13.593 --> 00:41:18.662
but memories of their horrifying
ordeal continue to haunt them.

525
00:41:18.664 --> 00:41:21.131
Cindy: Going through
this experience

526
00:41:21.133 --> 00:41:25.269
made me believe that
there is evil out here.

527
00:41:27.540 --> 00:41:30.674
We have nightmares
still. 15 years later.

528
00:41:30.676 --> 00:41:32.476
It'll always be with us.

529
00:41:32.478 --> 00:41:36.213
but we're getting
stronger about things.

530
00:41:41.353 --> 00:41:44.354
Narrator: The house remains
empty for quite some time

531
00:41:44.356 --> 00:41:48.225
until a couple from out
of town buys the place.

532
00:41:48.227 --> 00:41:49.693
Within a few months.

533
00:41:49.695 --> 00:41:52.763
their daughter encounters
an evil presence

534
00:41:52.765 --> 00:41:56.534
and the family
quickly moves out.
